# Environment variables (`.env`)

Secrets and instance-specific values live in **`.env`** at the repo root. **`.env` is gitignored** — commit only **`.env.example`** (placeholders).

## Variables (team standard)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **`BASE_URL`** | Metric Insights **instance** base URL (e.g. `https://your-org.metricinsights.com/`). Align with **`pp-dev.config.ts`** `backendBaseURL` when they describe the same backend. |
| **`APPLICATION_ID`** | MI application identifier (API / integrations as required). |
| **`APPLICATION_KEY`** | MI application key (API / integrations as required). |
| **`DEFAULT_USERNAME_ADMIN`** | Default **username** for Portal login during **development** and **testing** (local or scripted flows). |
| **`DEFAULT_PASSWORD_ADMIN`** | Default **password** for that user — **never** paste into committed files, Linear, or chat. |
| **`LINEAR_API_KEY`** | Optional **Linear** Personal API Key (`https://linear.app/settings/api`) for **`npm run ui-check:auth-linear`** / **`ui-check:linear-post`** when OAuth refresh fails. Never commit a real key. |
| **`FIGMA_API_KEY`** | **Figma** Personal Access Token (`https://www.figma.com/developers/api#access-tokens`) used by the **Figma MCP** server registered in **`.mcp.json`** / **`.cursor/mcp.json`** and by direct **Figma REST** calls (e.g. `curl -H "X-Figma-Token: $FIGMA_API_KEY" https://api.figma.com/v1/files/<fileKey>`). Used by **`.cursor/skills/ai-development/SKILL.md`** (Figma section) and **`.cursor/skills/figma-code-connect/SKILL.md`**. Never commit a real token. |

## Rules for agents

1. **Testing** (see **`.cursor/skills/ai-testing/SKILL.md`**): prefer **`DEFAULT_USERNAME_ADMIN`** / **`DEFAULT_PASSWORD_ADMIN`** from **`.env`** for Playwright, curl cookie sessions, or documented manual login — not hardcoded strings in repo sources.
2. **Development** (see **`.cursor/skills/ai-development/SKILL.md`**): same — use **`.env`** for local login and any script that needs admin; keep **`BASE_URL`** / keys consistent with **`pp-dev.config.ts`** and MI docs.
3. **Override:** process env **`PP_USER`** / **`PP_PASS`** may still override defaults for one-off runs; **`PP_LOCAL_APP_URL`** (optional) overrides the Playwright entry URL.
4. Load **`.env`** in Node automation via **`dotenv`** (see **`scripts/pp-ui-check-auth-and-linear-attach.mjs`**) or export vars in the shell before commands — do not commit populated **`.env`**.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env locally; never git add .env
```
